{"version":"1.2","person":{"datePublished":"2023-11-16","name":"Robert de Whitney","nameForms":[{"lang":"en","fullText":"Robert de Whitney","parts":[{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Given","value":"Robert"},{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Surname","value":"de Whitney"}],"order":"EUROTYPIC"}],"gender":"Male","lifespan":"1340–1402","fullLifespan":"Abt 1340–22 June 1402","birthDate":"+1340","birthPlace":{"address":"Whitney-on-Wye, Herefordshire, England","geo":{"latitude":52.12,"longitude":-3.0712,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"deathDate":"+1402-06-22","deathPlace":{"address":"Radnorshire, Wales, United Kingdom","geo":{"latitude":52.3301,"longitude":-3.3682,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"userCertifiedLifeSummary":"«b»Biography«/b»\nFather: Robert Whitney (1318-1380) (Mother unknown)\nborn: 1348\nMarried (at least twice):\nJanet/Joan Trussell\nMary/Maud Cromwell\n\n«b»Children:«/b»\n1.) Perryne Clanvowe\n\n2.) Joan Whitney (daughter by Janet Trussel), m (1) William Walwyn, (2) William Weldon\n\n3.) Thomas Whitney, fought at Agincourt in 1415\n\n4.) Robert Whitney (son by Maud Cromwell), m Wenllian Oldcastle\n\n«b»Died:«/b»\nbattle of Pillith, 1402\n\nSir Robert came of an old-established Herefordshire family, whose chief manor (held of the de Bohuns) was Whitney-on-Wye near the county boundary with Breconshire. He had presumably inherited the family estates by February 1361 (the date of his first mention) when he presented to the living at Pencombe near Bromyard.\n\n[previous paragraph may be for one Robert and following another. Missing from this writeup is that Sir Robert who was a member of Parliament 1377, 79, 80, was sent on to Milan in 1368 & his son (MP in 1391) was sent abroad in 1388.\n\nHe was sent abroad to negotiate treaty with Count of Flanders in 1388. Member of Parliament for Herefordshire in 1391. Sent to France to deliver Castle and Town of Cherbourg to King of Navarre in 1393. Knight Marshal at the Court of Richard II. Sent on the King's business to Ireland in 1394.\n\nHe fought against Owen Glendower at the battle of Pilleth on 22 June 1402, where he (together with his brother and other kinsmen) was slain.","sourceList":[{"title":"Our Royal, Titled, Noble, and Commoner Ancestors & Cousins","sourceType":"DEFAULT","sourceLink":"https://our-royal-titled-noble-and-commoner-ancestors.com/p1014.htm#i30449","sourceUri":"QWH4-PQS"}],"events":[{"name":"Birth","sources":"0","year":"1340","date":"Abt 1340","place":"Whitney-on-Wye, Herefordshire, England"},{"name":"Death of Parent","sources":"0","year":"1380","date":"1380","age":"40","id":"G27B-FQS"},{"name":"Birth of Child","sources":"0","year":"1387","date":"1387","place":"Whitney, Herefordshire, England","age":"47","id":"GNZS-BVT"},{"name":"Birth of Child","sources":"0","year":"1393","date":"1393","place":"Whitney, Herefordshire, England","age":"53","id":"G4C6-WRM"},{"name":"Death of Spouse","sources":"0","year":"1395","date":"1395","place":"Whitney, Herefordshire, England","age":"55","id":"LHR8-F61"},{"name":"Death","sources":"1","year":"1402","date":"22 June 1402","place":"Radnorshire, Wales, United Kingdom","age":"62"}],"parent":[{"name":"Robert Whitney","gender":"Male","lifespan":"1320–1380","birthDate":"+1320","deathDate":"+1380","age":60,"@type":"Person","identifier":"G27B-FQS","url":"https://ancestors.familysearch.org/en/G27B-FQS/robert-whitney-1320-1380","published":true}],"sibling":[{"name":"Robert de Whitney","gender":"Male","lifespan":"1340–1402","birthDate":"A+1340","deathDate":"+1402-06-22","age":62,"@type":"Person","identifier":"G8WY-VGL","url":"https://ancestors.familysearch.org/en/G8WY-VGL/robert-de-whitney-1340-1402","published":true}],"spouse":[{"name":"Mary Cromwell","gender":"Female","lifespan":"1352–1395","birthDate":"A+1352","deathDate":"+1395","age":43,"@type":"Person","identifier":"LHR8-F61","url":"https://ancestors.familysearch.org/en/LHR8-F61/mary-cromwell-1352-1395","published":true}],"children":[{"name":"Jane Whitney","gender"